<title>USA: Spectrum sues Acclaim.</title>
<headline>Spectrum sues Acclaim.</headline>
<dateline>ALAMEDA, Calif. 1997-01-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Spectrum HoloByte Inc Wednesday said it filed suit against Acclaim Entertainment Inc for breach of contract as a result of Acclaim's recent U.S. release of its Magic: The Gathering: 'BattleMage' PC CD-ROM title.</p>
<p>The complaint, filed in the U.S. District Court for the Northern District of California, states Acclaim's launch of the product is in breach of a settlement agreement between Acclaim and Spectrum.</p>
<p>The company said the settlement agreement ended earlier litigation over the two parties' respective license rights to the Magic: The Gathering card game and intellectual property. Spectrum said it is seeking unspecified monetary damages from Acclaim for breach of the terms of the agreement.</p>
